Issues.Body:
I have the following code:

```css
@theme {
  --text-shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px var(--tw-shadow-color);
  --text-shadow-md: 0 2px 4px var(--tw-shadow-color);
  --text-shadow-lg: 0 8px 16px var(--tw-shadow-color);
}

@utility text-shadow-* {
  text-shadow: --value(--text-shadow-*);
}
```




But I get the following error:



![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9f054ec7-4927-4618-8881-2394718bd128)

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7a18b583-4564-4629-871e-a6f4e83f0505)




Looking at the guide, I followed the example [here](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/adding-custom-styles#functional-utilities) but had to name it `text-shadow` instead of `text `because it was being picked up in the color namespace. 

My current solution is to use `textShadow `in the theme:

```css
@theme {
  --textShadow-sm: 0 1px 2px var(--tw-shadow-color);
  --textShadow-md: 0 2px 4px var(--tw-shadow-color);
  --textShadow-lg: 0 8px 16px var(--tw-shadow-color);
}

@utility text-shadow-* {
  text-shadow: --value(--textShadow);
}
```

This seems to be a bug.

In the current Tailwind CSS functionality, we may need to perform some static analysis on existing projects, including parsing the project's CSS, obtaining the AST, and performing transformations (similar to PostCSS's API). 

However, the currently exposed API does not provide such capabilities. Therefore, the purpose of this PR is to introduce these changes.

```ts
import { CSS, parseCss, CompileOptions } from 'tailwindcss'

function getContext(css: string, opts: CompileOptions = {}) {
  return parseCss(CSS.parse(css), opts)
}

const ctx = await getContext('@import \'tailwindcss\';')
// do stuff
// ...
```

Tailwind v4.0.6
@tailwindcss/vite 4.0.6

This keyframe statement (not in a config file, just in my css file
```
@keyframes rotate-cover {
	0% {
		transform: scale(1);
		z-index: 1;
	}
	50% {
		z-index: 10;
		transform: scale(1.15);
		filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0.75rem crimson);
		&:before {
			opacity: 1;
		}
	}
	100% {
		z-index: 1;
		transform: scale(1);
	}
}
```
Gets transformed on build to:
```
@keyframes rotate-cover{0%{z-index:1;transform:scale(1)}100%{z-index:1;transform:scale(1)}
```

The 50% step is just left out.

